The governing body of Harford County may grant, by law, a property tax credit under this section against the county property tax imposed on:
real property that is:
owned by any incorporated community association:
used as a public park, playground, or picnic area;
property that is:
owned by the Habonim Camp Association Company, Incorporated;
used only for the purposes of the Habonim Camp Association Company; and
in excess of the property exempted under § 7-202 of this article;
property that is owned by the Maryland Ornithological Society, Incorporated;
real property that is:
owned by the North Harford Game and Fish Association, Incorporated;
located on Wheeler School Road; and
used only for the purposes of the association;
real property that is:
owned by the trustees of the Ladew Topiary Gardens;
located on Jarrettsville Pike;
used only for the purposes of the Ladew Topiary Gardens; and
in excess of the property exempted under § 7-202 of this article;
real property that:
is used primarily for an agricultural purpose; and
does not have an agricultural use assessment;
real property that is:
used primarily for amateur sports events; and
owned by the Havre de Grace Little League, Incorporated;
real property, only after July 1, 1988, that:
is located in an agricultural district under an original or renewed agreement to be located within an agricultural district; or
becomes subject to an agricultural preservation easement that has been conveyed to the Maryland Agricultural Land Preservation Foundation;
real property that is:
owned by a Harford County volunteer fire or ambulance company;
held for the future use as a station or substation site, as approved by the Harford County Volunteer Fire and Ambulance Association in their 5-year plan; and
not exempt under § 7-209 of this article;
subject to the condition established under paragraph (4) of this subsection, owner-occupied residential real property:
that is determined by the governing body of Harford County to have been adversely impacted by its proximity to the refuse disposal system;
real property, only after July 1, 1993, that:
is located in the Harford County Agricultural District in accordance with the Harford County Agricultural Land Preservation Program under Chapter 60 of the Harford County Code; or
becomes subject to an agricultural preservation easement that has been conveyed to Harford County in accordance with the Harford County Agricultural Land Preservation Program, under Chapter 60 of the Harford County Code;
subject to paragraph (6) of this subsection, real property that is new construction or a substantial improvement to the real property of a commercial or industrial business that:
is or will be doing business in Harford County; and
will employ at least 12 additional full-time local employees by the second year the credit is allowed;
subject to paragraph (7) of this subsection, real property:
that is located in a Rural Legacy Area as defined in § 5-9A-02 of the Natural Resources Article; and
for which the property owner has sold the development rights under the Rural Legacy Program established under Title 5, Subtitle 9A of the Natural Resources Article; and
real property:
that is adjacent to property that is:
that was subdivided from the adjacent property, withdrawn from the agricultural district or agricultural easement, and conveyed to a child of the owner of the adjacent property under a child lot exclusion to build a home on the property; and
the owner of which:

The governing body of Harford County or of a municipal corporation in Harford County may grant, by law, a property tax credit under this section against the county or municipal corporation property tax imposed on real property that is:
owned by any person who:
constructs a housing structure; or
operates a housing project;
used for a housing structure or project which may contain a community service facility;
a structure constructed or substantially rehabilitated under § 8 of the United States Housing Act of 1937 primarily for occupancy by elderly individuals;
receiving rent subsidy; and
operated on a nonprofit or limited distribution basis.

In this subsection, "facility" means a continuing care facility for the aged that:
provides continuing care as defined in § 10-401 of the Human Services Article;
is licensed as a related institution under Title 19, Subtitle 3 of the Health - General Article;
is certified by the Department of Aging; and
is exempt from federal income tax under § 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code or is owned or operated by a person that is exempt from federal income tax under § 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code.

The governing body of Harford County or of a municipal corporation in Harford County may provide, by law, for:
the amount and duration of the tax credit under this subsection;
additional eligibility criteria for the tax credit under this subsection;
regulations and procedures for the application and uniform processing of requests for the tax credit; and
any other provision necessary to carry out the credit under this subsection.
